description.p:
(i) a 0.5% to saturated solution of ammonium sulfate or bisulfate in concentrated sulfuric acid at a temperature of from about 10 (degree)  C. to 340 (degree)  C.;


(ii) a slurry of 10% to 90% ammonium sulfate or bisulfate in concentrated sulfuric acid at a temperature of from about 10 (degree)  C. to 255 (degree)  C.;


(iii) crystals or granules or flakes of ammonium sulfate at a temperature of from about 10 (degree)  C. to 255 (degree)  C.;


(iv) molten ammonium sulfate at >280 (degree)  C. and ammonium bisulfate at a temperature of from about 145 (degree)  C.;


(v) a 0.5% to saturated solution of ammonium sulfate in water at a temperature of from about 10 (degree)  C. to 110 (degree)  C.; or


(vi) a slurry of from about 10%-90% of ammonium sulfate in water at a temperature of from about 10 (degree)  C. to 110 (degree)  C.
